警察局决不容忍有反抗和异议的存在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This police department does not tolerate dissent, or contradiction,{\r}

596
00:40:25,402 --> 00:40:27,802
甚至是让他们难堪的情况
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}or even embarrassment.{\r}

597
00:40:27,871 --> 00:40:32,638
而你，你让他们脸上很不好看 这让他们很不高兴
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And you are in a position to embarrass them and they do not like it.{\r}

598
00:40:32,709 --> 00:40:35,576
他们会利用一切的手段来诋毁你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They will do anything in their power to discredit you.{\r}

599
00:40:35,646 --> 00:40:39,241
我不知道见过多少次了，现在已经开始麻木了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've seen that happen too many times to start going blind now.{\r}

600
00:40:39,316 --> 00:40:41,375
所以我才想要见见你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That's why I wanted to meet you,{\r}

601
00:40:41,451 --> 00:40:44,284
我要告诉你，你让自己陷入了怎样的境地
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}to let you know what you're getting yourself into{\r}

602
00:40:44,354 --> 00:40:47,812
而且我希望能帮助你抗争到底 如果你是这样决定的话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and to help you fight it, if you choose to.{\r}

603
00:40:47,891 --> 00:40:50,291
牧师先生，很感谢你为我做的一切
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Reverend, I appreciate everything that you're doing{\r}

604
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:53,761
还有你所告诉我的信息
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and everything that you said,{\r}

605
00:40:54,665 --> 00:40:56,724
但是我没有这样的想法
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}but I'm not on a mission.{\r}

606
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,825
我只想找我的儿子回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I just want my son home.{\r}

607
00:41:00,804 --> 00:41:03,102
柯林斯太太，有不知多少母亲的孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins, a lot of mothers' sons{\r}

608
00:41:03,173 --> 00:41:06,336
已经因为这一点便宜私利而成为了牺牲品
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}have been sacrificed to expediency around here.{\r}

609
00:41:06,410 --> 00:41:08,708
你的孩子，很遗憾，肯定不是第一个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your son, unfortunately, would not be the first.{\r}

610
00:41:08,779 --> 00:41:12,146
但如果你能做出正确的选择，也许他将是最后一个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But if you do it right, he may very well be the last.{\r}

611
00:41:20,123 --> 00:41:22,455
他只有两条路来选
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He had two cavities that needed filling.{\r}

612
00:41:22,526 --> 00:41:25,188
由他来引出这次战斗，而我负责处理
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He put up a fight, but I took care of it.{\r}

613
00:41:25,262 --> 00:41:26,524
还有呢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And?{\r}

614
00:41:26,597 --> 00:41:30,260
你儿子的门牙之间有条缝，也就是齿隙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your son's upper front teeth were separated by a small tissue, a diastema.{\r}

615
00:41:30,334 --> 00:41:32,825
两颗牙齿之间大约有1/8英寸的距离
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It made them sit about an eighth of an inch apart.{\r}

616
00:41:32,903 --> 00:41:35,337
房间里那孩子的嘴里却没有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The boy in that room has no such gap.{\r}

617
00:41:35,405 --> 00:41:37,669
牙齿也会随年龄改变么？他们是这么宣称的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Can that change with age? Because that's what they're gonna say.{\r}

618
00:41:37,741 --> 00:41:39,174
在某些情况下，的确是有可能的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}In some cases, yes, it's possible.{\r}

619
00:41:39,242 --> 00:41:42,541
但是沃特牙齿之间的那条缝是不可能长拢的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But the tissue between Walter's teeth prevents that from happening.{\r}

620
00:41:42,613 --> 00:41:45,980
不通过手术是无法办到的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}See, they can never come together without an operation to sever the tissue,{\r}

621
00:41:46,049 --> 00:41:49,746
而且我现在就可以明确地告诉你说 他从来没有接受过这样的手术
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and I can tell you right now that he has never had such an operation.{\r}

622
00:41:50,721 --> 00:41:53,189
你能不能将这些话写到证词里？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Would you be willing to put that officially in writing?{\r}

623
00:41:53,256 --> 00:41:56,020
请原谅我的粗鲁，我绝对帮你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Pardon my language, but hell yes.{\r}

624
00:41:57,661 --> 00:42:00,926
看来麻药的效果过去了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sounds like the anesthetic's wearing off.{\r}

625
00:42:00,998 --> 00:42:04,365
或者，我应该先去写证词
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}On the other hand, maybe I'll write that letter first.{\r}

626
00:42:04,434 --> 00:42:07,494
给这个小家伙一点时间好好想想
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Give the little fella something to think about.{\r}

627
00:42:17,581 --> 00:42:19,378
如果真是那样的话，他的变化也太大了点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, if it is, he's changed enormously.{\r}

628
00:42:19,449 --> 00:42:21,349
你知道我是谁吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you know who I am?{\r}

629
00:42:21,418 --> 00:42:22,715
你是个老师
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're a teacher.{\r}

630
00:42:22,786 --> 00:42:25,949
没错，但是老师也有名字啊？ 我的名字叫什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, but even teachers have names. What's mine?{\r}

631
00:42:26,823 --> 00:42:28,654
我不记得了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't remember.{\r}

632
00:42:28,725 --> 00:42:31,558
我认识你，但是我不记得你的名字了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I know you, but I don't remember your name.{\r}

633
00:42:32,863 --> 00:42:35,195
是福克斯太太 好了，去你位置坐下吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Fox. Now, take your seat.{\r}

634
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:54,273
我说的不是让你坐下，是让你回自己位子坐下 安排给你的那个位子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't say take a seat. I said take your seat, the one assigned you.{\r}

635
00:42:54,351 --> 00:42:59,015
你应该知道自己的位子在哪里 你可是坐了快一年了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You must know where it is, you've been sitting in it for over a year now.{\r}

636
00:43:07,197 --> 00:43:10,792
柯林斯太太, 如果他是你的儿子 我就把教尺吃下去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins, if that's your son, I'll eat my yardstick.{\r}

637
00:43:10,867 --> 00:43:14,268
我不仅会帮你提供证明，我还愿意到法庭上给你作证
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Not only will I put it in writing, I will testify to it in a court of law{\r}

638
00:43:14,337 --> 00:43:18,068
如果需要的话，我可以给卡尔文・柯立兹总统写信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}or to the President Calvin Coolidge himself if I have to.{\r}

639
00:43:19,276 --> 00:43:20,368
谢谢你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}

640
00:43:23,180 --> 00:43:25,273
今天晚上的广播见
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll see you tonight for the broadcast.{\r}

641
00:43:25,348 --> 00:43:26,679
祝你好运
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Good luck.{\r}

642
00:43:35,926 --> 00:43:37,154
就几个问题，女士
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Quick question, ma'am.{\r}

643
00:43:37,227 --> 00:43:38,421
就几个问题
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Quick question!{\r}

644
00:43:38,495 --> 00:43:40,224
柯林斯太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins.{\r}

645
00:43:41,465 --> 00:43:43,558
你好，我的名字是克莉斯汀・柯林斯.
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello. My name is Christine Collins.{\r}

646
00:43:43,633 --> 00:43:45,828
早上好 早上好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Good morning. Good morning.{\r}

647
00:43:45,902 --> 00:43:50,464
在3月10号，我9岁大的儿子沃特・柯林斯失踪了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}On March 10th, my nine-year-old son, Walter Collins, disappeared.{\r}

648
00:43:50,540 --> 00:43:52,269
经过5个月的调查
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And a five-month investigation{\r}

649
00:43:52,342 --> 00:43:56,301
他们从伊利诺斯州的德卡博带回来一个男孩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}led to a boy being brought to Los Angeles from DeKalb, Illinois.{\r}

650
00:43:57,380 --> 00:44:00,747
他们告诉我，也告诉大家说这个孩子就是我的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They told me and all of you that this boy was my son.{\r}

651
00:44:00,851 --> 00:44:02,682
他其实不是我的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was not my son.{\r}

652
00:44:02,753 --> 00:44:04,687
洛杉矶警局弄错了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The LAPD made a mistake,{\r}

653
00:44:04,755 --> 00:44:08,452
因为这个孩子的变化太大了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and that is the reason for the supposed transformation.{\r}

654
00:44:09,059 --> 00:44:10,993
我这里有他的医生和老师提供的证明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have letters from his teachers and his doctors{\r}

655
00:44:11,061 --> 00:44:13,461
都能够证明他不是我的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}all confirming that he is not my son.{\r}

656
00:44:13,530 --> 00:44:17,660
我已经拿去复印了，明天我就拿给你看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm having them reprinted now, and I'll have them for you tomorrow.{\r}

657
00:44:17,734 --> 00:44:21,192
我给了洛杉矶警局好多次机会来纠正他们的错误
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have given the LAPD every opportunity to admit their mistake{\r}

658
00:44:21,271 --> 00:44:23,535
还有重新开始搜索我的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and renew the search for my son.{\r}

659
00:44:23,607 --> 00:44:25,507
但他们一直拒绝那样做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Since they have refused to do so,{\r}

660
00:44:25,575 --> 00:44:28,476
所以我不得不把事情公之于众
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}it has forced me to bring my case public.{\r}

661
00:44:28,545 --> 00:44:32,242
我希望这样做能说服他们 把这个问题给圆满处理好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I hope that this now will persuade them to finish what they started{\r}

662
00:44:32,315 --> 00:44:34,977
然后把我真正的儿子送回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and bring my son home to me.{\r}

663
00:44:35,051 --> 00:44:36,541
谢谢大家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you very much.{\r}

664
00:44:49,699 --> 00:44:50,927
莫雷利！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Morelli!{\r}

665
00:44:51,535 --> 00:44:53,901
我要你去找那个叫柯林斯的女人，带到这里来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I want you to find the Collins woman and get her here.{\r}

666
00:44:53,970 --> 00:44:56,200
还有，比尔，带她从后门进来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And, Bill, bring her in the back way.{\r}

667
00:44:56,273 --> 00:44:57,331
是，长官
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir.{\r}

668
00:45:08,318 --> 00:45:09,842
这边，女士
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This way, miss.{\r}

669
00:45:10,887 --> 00:45:11,945
为什么我们要从后面绕？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why are we going in the back?{\r}

670
00:45:12,022 --> 00:45:14,786
这是上尉的命令，前面都是记者
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Captain's orders. Front's jammed with reporters.{\r}

671
00:45:19,729 --> 00:45:22,425
太太，请坐，琼斯上尉马上就过来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please, sit down, miss. Captain Jones'll be right with you.{\r}

672
00:45:22,499 --> 00:45:26,799
嘿，有人要接手加拿大的案子么， 伊巴拉你空着么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey! Anyone want to take a call from the Canadian Mounties? Ybarra?{\r}

673
00:45:26,903 --> 00:45:28,165
他们怎么了？丢了头麋鹿？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What'd they do, lose a moose?{\r}

674
00:45:28,238 --> 00:45:31,469
他们要抓一个从加拿大偷渡过来的小鬼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They need a juvenile living here illegally deported back to Canada.{\r}

675
00:45:31,541 --> 00:45:34,942
他和他的表哥一起住在怀恩威尔河边的一座农场里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's living with his cousin on some ranch near Riverside, in Wineville.{\r}

676
00:45:35,011 --> 00:45:36,069
你来接？ 我来接
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You want it? I'll take it.{\r}

677
00:45:36,146 --> 00:45:37,204
我空的实在没事做了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Got nothing better to do.{\r}

678
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:38,713
你简直就是个王子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're a prince.{\r}

679
00:45:41,184 --> 00:45:42,617
柯林斯太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins.{\r}

680
00:45:42,686 --> 00:45:45,883
你可以让这男孩待在这儿，她会照顾好他的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can leave the boy. She'll take care of him.{\r}

681
00:45:51,061 --> 00:45:52,289
请坐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sit.{\r}

682
00:45:52,896 --> 00:45:55,763
你给我们造了不小的麻烦啊，柯林斯太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, you've caused us quite a bit of trouble, Mrs. Collins.{\r}

683
00:45:55,832 --> 00:45:58,858
整个警察局都对这样的情况感到很失望
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This situation has become an embarrassment for the entire police department.{\r}

684
00:45:58,935 --> 00:46:00,459
我没有想要让任何人尴尬
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It wasn't my intention to embarrass anyone.{\r}

685
00:46:00,537 --> 00:46:02,004
哦，当然不是，你当然不想
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, no, of course not.{\r}

686
00:46:02,072 --> 00:46:05,769
作为对我们的回报，你告诉报纸说我们连几个孩子都分不清？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You just told the papers we couldn't tell one boy from another as a compliment{\r}

687
00:46:05,842 --> 00:46:08,037
为了你这个案子我们忙了好几个月
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}for the months we spent working on your case.{\r}

688
00:46:08,111 --> 00:46:10,477
你是把我们都当白痴吗？是不是？你很开心吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You trying to make fools out of us? Is that it? You enjoy this?{\r}

689
00:46:10,547 --> 00:46:12,674
我没有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course not.{\r}

690
00:46:12,749 --> 00:46:13,977
我希望你们能找到我的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I want you to find my son.{\r}

691
00:46:14,050 --> 00:46:15,813
你知道你的问题在哪里吗？柯林斯太太？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You know what your problem is, Mrs. Collins?{\r}

692
00:46:15,886 --> 00:46:17,820
你只是想逃避一个母亲应尽的责任
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're trying to shirk your responsibilities as a mother.{\r}

693
00:46:17,888 --> 00:46:19,048
你说什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

694
00:46:19,122 --> 00:46:21,181
你不想要个拖油瓶，对不对？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You enjoyed being a free woman, didn't you?{\r}

695
00:46:21,258 --> 00:46:23,317
你只是不想要有孩子拖累吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You enjoyed not having to worry about a young son.{\r}

696
00:46:23,393 --> 00:46:25,918
那样你就可以去自己想去的地方 做自己想做的事情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You could go where you wanted, do whatever you wanted,{\r}

697
00:46:25,996 --> 00:46:27,793
还有见任何你想见的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}see anyone you wanted.{\r}

698
00:46:27,864 --> 00:46:30,355
结果我们找到了你的儿子，而且我们把他带了回来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But then we found your son, and we brought him back.{\r}

699
00:46:30,433 --> 00:46:32,663
现在他又变成了你的负累
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And now he's an inconvenience to you.{\r}

700
00:46:32,736 --> 00:46:35,534
所以你才炮制了这个谎言
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And that's why you cooked up this scheme,{\r}

701
00:46:35,605 --> 00:46:38,438
好把这个孩子丢给州政府，让政府来帮你抚养他长大
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}to throw him to the state and get the state to raise him for you.{\r}

702
00:46:38,508 --> 00:46:40,271
是不是这样？ 才不是这样！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't that true? That is not true!{\r}

703
00:46:40,343 --> 00:46:42,675
不是？就连那个孩子自己都说是你的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No? Well, even the boy says he's your son.{\r}

704
00:46:42,746 --> 00:46:44,043
他为什么会那么说？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why would he say that?{\r}

705
