{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope your stay here has convinced you not to try crossing the border{\r}

947
01:02:12,141 --> 01:02:13,904
以后不会再偷偷越境了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}illegally in the future.{\r}

948
01:02:14,043 --> 01:02:15,135
等等！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wait!{\r}

949
01:02:17,279 --> 01:02:20,510
我想跟带我进来的那位长官谈谈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd like to talk to the officer who brought me in.{\r}

950
01:02:20,583 --> 01:02:22,380
我想他这会儿有更重要的事情要做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sure he has far more important things...{\r}

951
01:02:22,451 --> 01:02:24,749
求你了，是很重要的事情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please. It's important.{\r}

952
01:02:31,594 --> 01:02:33,255
克莉斯汀・柯林斯.
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Christine Collins.{\r}

953
01:02:33,329 --> 01:02:35,991
谢谢 柯林斯太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you. Mrs. Collins.{\r}

954
01:02:37,766 --> 01:02:40,496
我是乔纳森・斯蒂尔医生 请坐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Dr. Jonathan Steele. Please, have a seat.{\r}

955
01:02:48,210 --> 01:02:51,577
我希望你在这里过得还算不错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope your stay with us has been comfortable so far.{\r}

956
01:02:52,514 --> 01:02:53,640
嗯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

957
01:02:54,149 --> 01:02:55,616
真的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Really?{\r}

958
01:02:55,718 --> 01:02:59,176
我以为第一次进来都会比较难受
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd think it'd be quite difficult at first.{\r}

959
01:03:01,824 --> 01:03:03,018
的确如此
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, it was.{\r}

960
01:03:03,092 --> 01:03:06,892
当然不好受，不过我觉得还多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course it was very difficult, but comfortable enough.{\r}

961
01:03:17,206 --> 01:03:20,573
我看到他们做了… 他们抽了血做测试
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I see that they have... They've taken a blood test.{\r}

962
01:03:21,844 --> 01:03:23,607
瓦色尔曼氏测试
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The Wassermman Test.{\r}

963
01:03:23,679 --> 01:03:27,809
他们说是为了检查有没有梅毒 梅毒会影响大脑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They said it was to check for syphilis, 'cause it affects the mind.{\r}

964
01:03:27,917 --> 01:03:31,717
听到别人觉得你应该去检查梅毒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The idea that someone thinks you need to be checked for syphilis,{\r}

965
01:03:31,787 --> 01:03:33,652
你会不会觉得很沮丧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}does that upset you?{\r}

966
01:03:33,722 --> 01:03:36,054
不会，他们说只是依照惯例，我不觉得有问题
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, they said it was standard procedure, so it did not.{\r}

967
01:03:36,125 --> 01:03:38,525
对，当然，标准流程
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, exactly. Standard procedure.{\r}

968
01:03:38,594 --> 01:03:40,459
我们必须做到面面俱到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We have to cover all our bases.{\r}

969
01:03:40,529 --> 01:03:41,962
我可以理解
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can imagine{\r}

970
01:03:44,266 --> 01:03:46,928
也许对有些人来说会不好受
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}that for some people that would be uncomfortable,{\r}

971
01:03:47,002 --> 01:03:49,163
我可以理解
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}but I understood.{\r}

972
01:04:07,690 --> 01:04:13,026
根据你的记录，你怀疑警察
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}According to your file you believe that the police substituted{\r}

973
01:04:13,128 --> 01:04:15,221
用假的男孩来冒充你的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}a fake boy for your son.{\r}

974
01:04:15,297 --> 01:04:17,492
我不是说的真假
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I didn't say he was a fake boy.{\r}

975
01:04:17,566 --> 01:04:19,659
他不是我的孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's not my boy.{\r}

976
01:04:19,735 --> 01:04:21,168
他们找错孩子了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They brought home the wrong boy.{\r}

977
01:04:21,236 --> 01:04:23,204
我的儿子依然不见踪影
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My son is still missing.{\r}

978
01:04:23,405 --> 01:04:28,274
是吗？那就奇怪了，因为我在这张报纸上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, that's strange, because I have here a newspaper article{\r}

979
01:04:28,744 --> 01:04:34,239
看到了一张你在火车站迎接儿子回家的照片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}with a photo of you at the train station, welcoming home your son.{\r}

980
01:04:37,119 --> 01:04:39,314
这照片上的人是你没错吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That is you in the photo, isn't it?{\r}

981
01:04:39,888 --> 01:04:40,912
是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

982
01:04:40,990 --> 01:04:42,082
确定？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah.{\r}

983
01:04:42,791 --> 01:04:43,815
是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

984
01:04:43,892 --> 01:04:46,827
也就是说，一开始他是你的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, at first he was your son,{\r}

985
01:04:48,330 --> 01:04:50,127
然后现在他又不是你儿子了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and now he's not your son.{\r}

986
01:04:52,101 --> 01:04:54,001
这样的情况存在多长时间了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Has this been going on for a long time?{\r}

987
01:04:54,069 --> 01:04:57,698
人会长大，变成其他的样子？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}People changing, becoming something other than what they are?{\r}

988
01:04:57,773 --> 01:04:59,638
人不会变
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}People don't change.{\r}

989
01:04:59,708 --> 01:05:01,266
你觉得人不会改变？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't think people change?{\r}

990
01:05:01,343 --> 01:05:02,435
不是，我不是…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, that's not...{\r}

991
01:05:06,081 --> 01:05:08,345
他们逼迫过你吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The police, they're not out to persecute you?{\r}

992
01:05:08,417 --> 01:05:10,777
没有，他们没有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, they're not.{\r}

993
01:05:10,853 --> 01:05:13,947
警察是来保护你的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The police are here to protect you.{\r}

994
01:05:14,723 --> 01:05:15,985
是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

995
01:05:16,225 --> 01:05:17,658
你确定？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Really?{\r}

996
01:05:17,726 --> 01:05:18,784
是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

997
01:05:19,862 --> 01:05:24,231
这就更奇怪了，因为你一开始被送进来的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, that's odd because when you were admitted,{\r}

998
01:05:25,200 --> 01:05:31,435
告诉我们的护士长说 警察想要给你一个惩罚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}you told the head nurse that the police were conspiring deliberately to punish you.{\r}

999
01:05:31,573 --> 01:05:35,976
是护士长和实习生都有份惩罚你？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, either the head nurse and the interns are also conspiring to punish you{\r}

1000
01:05:36,045 --> 01:05:38,275
还是你的故事内容又变了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}or you're changing your story.{\r}

1001
01:05:44,586 --> 01:05:50,616
你是不是经常会分不清现实和幻想，柯林斯太太？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you often have trouble telling reality from fantasy, Mrs. Collins?{\r}

1002
01:05:53,095 --> 01:05:54,119
没有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

1003
01:06:06,008 --> 01:06:08,033
抱歉这种天气里还把你叫出来，警探先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry to bring you out in this weather, Detective,{\r}

1004
01:06:08,110 --> 01:06:10,101
但是这孩子一直很抗拒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}but the boy has been quite insistent.{\r}

1005
01:06:10,179 --> 01:06:11,544
那也很正常
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's all right.{\r}

1006
01:06:11,613 --> 01:06:14,548
我先来听听他想要说什么 然后回家把自己弄干
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll see what he has to say so I can go home and get dry.{\r}

1007
01:06:14,616 --> 01:06:17,244
这种下雨天 外面到处都是阿猫阿狗和民主党人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's raining cats, dogs, and Democrats out there,{\r}

1008
01:06:17,319 --> 01:06:19,617
所以最好别让我白跑一趟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}so this had better be worth it.{\r}

1009
01:06:20,189 --> 01:06:21,713
又是你？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You again, huh?{\r}

1010
01:06:28,363 --> 01:06:29,557
让我们看看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll see.{\r}

1011
01:06:33,302 --> 01:06:34,394
好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well?{\r}

1012
01:06:37,239 --> 01:06:38,467
很不容易，对吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This isn't easy, okay?{\r}

1013
01:06:38,540 --> 01:06:39,529
什么意思？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah?{\r}

1014
01:06:39,608 --> 01:06:42,941
大老远地冒着暴雨开车过来也不是件容易事
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Driving my ass here in the pouring rain wasn't easy either.{\r}

1015
01:06:44,613 --> 01:06:47,377
高顿・诺斯考特是我的表弟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My cousin is Gordon Northcott.{\r}

1016
01:06:47,449 --> 01:06:50,043
你找到我的那个农庄是他的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He owns the ranch where you found me.{\r}

1017
01:06:51,053 --> 01:06:55,046
他说我可以在他离开的时候替他照顾这儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He said I could live there in exchange I watch the place when he's gone,{\r}

1018
01:06:55,924 --> 01:06:58,085
打打杂，干干家务之类的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}doing chores and stuff like that.{\r}

1019
01:06:59,628 --> 01:07:02,426
还说我可以想待多久就待多久
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Said I could stay as long as I wanted to.{\r}

1020
01:07:03,398 --> 01:07:06,128
于是我就以为我也可以随时离开
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I thought that meant I could leave whenever I wanted.{\r}

1021
01:07:06,201 --> 01:07:07,259
~
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mmm.{\r}

1022
01:07:07,336 --> 01:07:09,634
你的意思是说他把你当囚犯一样关了起来？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You saying that he held you prisoner?{\r}

1023
01:07:09,705 --> 01:07:10,865
胡扯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bull.{\r}

1024
01:07:10,939 --> 01:07:13,806
我去的时候可是看到你自由的像只松鸦一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}When I got there, you were running around free as a jaybird.{\r}

1025
01:07:13,876 --> 01:07:15,810
只要你愿意，随时都可以离开嘛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Could've left any time you wanted.{\r}

1026
01:07:15,878 --> 01:07:16,902
不是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

1027
01:07:17,012 --> 01:07:18,741
那又是什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, what's this, huh?{\r}

1028
01:07:18,847 --> 01:07:20,872
随便编造一个故事 好解释你为什么会非法入境？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Some kind of story to cover why you're in the country illegally?{\r}

1029
01:07:20,949 --> 01:07:22,075
不，不是那样的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, it's nothing like that.{\r}

1030
01:07:22,151 --> 01:07:23,209
我也没兴趣听你讲故事，你懂么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}'Cause I don't have time for this, okay?{\r}

1031
01:07:23,285 --> 01:07:24,445
听我说！他说…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Listen to me! He said...{\r}

1032
01:07:24,520 --> 01:07:25,782
说什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

1033
01:07:25,854 --> 01:07:27,583
他说了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What did he say?{\r}

1034
01:07:27,656 --> 01:07:30,955
他说如果我敢走人的话，他就把我干掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He said that if I tried to leave, he'd kill me.{\r}

1035
01:07:31,026 --> 01:07:34,052
听着，你不明白他是怎样一个人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, you don't understand what he's like,{\r}

1036
01:07:34,129 --> 01:07:37,462
还有…他做了什么，他逼我做了什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}what he... What we did, what he made me do.{\r}

1037
01:07:39,968 --> 01:07:41,435
好吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All right.{\r}

1038
01:07:41,503 --> 01:07:43,937
那我们从头说起
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's start at the beginning then.{\r}

1039
01:07:47,576 --> 01:07:49,669
他逼你做了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What'd he make you do?{\r}

1040
01:07:55,050 --> 01:07:56,449
我们杀了一些小孩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We killed some kids.{\r}

1041
01:07:56,518 --> 01:07:57,780
你说什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

1042
01:07:57,853 --> 01:08:01,448
你听我说，我不想干的，我发誓 是他逼我帮他杀人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, I didn't mean to, I swear. He made me help him.{\r}

1043
01:08:01,523 --> 01:08:04,117
他说如果我不动手的话，他会连我也一起杀掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He said if I didn't, he'd kill me, too.{\r}

1044
01:08:04,193 --> 01:08:06,889
你得帮帮我，求求你了，我很害怕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, you gotta help me, please. I'm so scared.{\r}

1045
01:08:06,962 --> 01:08:09,954
我不想因为杀小孩下地狱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't want to go to hell for killing kids.{\r}

1046
01:08:10,032 --> 01:08:11,397
你看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look.{\r}

1047
01:08:11,466 --> 01:08:14,299
什么孩子，你到底…你到底在讲什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What kids? What... What are you talking about?{\r}

1048
01:08:14,369 --> 01:08:16,894
我不知道，我根本不知道他们的名字
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know. I never knew their names.{\r}

1049
01:08:16,972 --> 01:08:18,462
名字？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Names?{\r}

1050
01:08:18,540 --> 01:08:19,564
多少个？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How many?{\r}

1051
01:08:19,641 --> 01:08:21,131
多少孩子？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How many kids?{\r}

1052
01:08:21,210 --> 01:08:22,575
一共加起来？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All together?{\r}

1053
01:08:26,982 --> 01:08:28,847
大概有20个吧，我想
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}About 20, I guess.{\r}

1054
01:08:30,219 --> 01:08:31,618
不，你在撒谎
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, you're lying.{\r}

1055
01:08:31,687 --> 01:08:34,053
我没有，我发誓都是真的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No! It's true, I swear!{\r}

1056
01:08:34,122 --> 01:08:35,783
你难道要告诉我说你杀了20个小孩？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're gonna tell me you killed 20 kids?{\r}

1057
01:08:35,857 --> 01:08:39,315
嗯！大概那么多
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah! Thereabouts.{\r}

1058
01:08:41,663 --> 01:08:44,063
我后来就没有数了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I stopped counting after a while.{\r}

1059
01:08:47,903 --> 01:08:51,669
高顿说大概有1、2个逃跑了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Gordon said maybe one or two may have escaped.{\r}

1060
01:08:55,377 --> 01:08:56,401
但是…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But...{\r}

1061
01:08:56,478 --> 01:08:57,502
不可能
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

1062
01:08:57,579 --> 01:09:00,412
不可能有人杀了20个孩子好吗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Nobody can just up and kill 20 kids, okay?{\r}

1063
01:09:00,482 --> 01:09:01,676
我们真的做了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We did.{\r}

1064
01:09:04,086 --> 01:09:05,280
是我们杀的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We did.{\r}

1065
01:09:08,190 --> 01:09:09,248
怎么杀的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How?{\r}

1066
01:09:11,360 --> 01:09:13,726
大多数时候我们就杀一两个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Most times we'd just have one or two.{\r}

1067
01:09:15,364 --> 01:09:17,298
有时候会是三个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sometimes as many as three.{\r}

