01:31:16,216 --> 01:31:18,776
他的马叫做托尼，你知道不？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}His horse is named Tony. Did you know that?{\r}

1428
01:31:23,089 --> 01:31:24,488
你觉得怎么样了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How are you feeling?{\r}

1429
01:31:24,558 --> 01:31:25,923
还好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All right.{\r}

1430
01:31:26,660 --> 01:31:28,389
还有一辆警察的车停在外面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The police still have a car outside.{\r}

1431
01:31:28,462 --> 01:31:32,330
我猜他们是想知道你接下去要做什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I guess they're waiting to see what your next move is going to be.{\r}

1432
01:31:33,467 --> 01:31:35,492
- 我要回家 - 然后呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm going home. And then?{\r}

1433
01:31:35,969 --> 01:31:37,903
然后，我能想到很多事情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Then, I've been giving it a lot of thought.{\r}

1434
01:31:37,971 --> 01:31:42,465
他们是怎么对待这些女人的 还有他们是怎么对待沃特的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And what they did to those women, and what they did about Walter.{\r}

1435
01:31:43,343 --> 01:31:47,006
我一直教他，永远不要主动动手，但要保证自己赢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I used to always tell him, "You never start a fight, but you always finish it. "{\r}

1436
01:31:47,080 --> 01:31:50,481
这次的事情不是我挑起来的，但是要由我来结束
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I didn't start this fight, but I'm gonna finish it.{\r}

1437
01:31:51,084 --> 01:31:55,282
柯林斯太太，你现在是个公众关注人物了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins, right now you're a sufficiently high profile that I think{\r}

1438
01:31:55,355 --> 01:31:59,189
我想，现在警察就算想派人跟着你，也要考虑一下了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}even the police would hesitate to go after you out in the open,{\r}

1439
01:31:59,659 --> 01:32:02,059
但是我必须警告你，事情的变化很快
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}but I have to warn you that could change very quickly{\r}

1440
01:32:02,128 --> 01:32:04,824
如果他们觉得自己的位置受到了威胁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}if they feel their position threatened.{\r}

1441
01:32:04,898 --> 01:32:06,695
整个风向都会变，真的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Very quickly indeed.{\r}

1442
01:32:08,068 --> 01:32:10,400
他们现在想怎么对付我？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What are they gonna do to me now?{\r}

1443
01:32:12,305 --> 01:32:13,932
他们没有证据
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They got nothing.{\r}

1444
01:32:16,943 --> 01:32:18,467
我要回家了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm going home.{\r}

1445
01:32:30,202 --> 01:32:33,601
加拿大，温哥华 1928年9月20日
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

1446
01:32:42,202 --> 01:32:43,601
嗨，姐姐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hi, sis.{\r}

1447
01:32:44,337 --> 01:32:45,668
高顿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Gordon.{\r}

1448
01:32:45,739 --> 01:32:48,230
我都不知道你回来了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't know you were back in town.{\r}

1449
01:32:48,909 --> 01:32:51,070
嗯，我几天前就回来了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, I got in a couple of days ago,{\r}

1450
01:32:51,144 --> 01:32:54,011
我想给你个惊喜，没有…没有什么问题吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}figured I'd surprise you. Is that... Is that okay?{\r}

1451
01:32:54,080 --> 01:32:57,106
当然，当然没有 进来吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes. Yes, of course. Of course, come on in.{\r}

1452
01:33:00,020 --> 01:33:02,318
我那个小侄女呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Where's that little niece of mine?{\r}

1453
01:33:02,389 --> 01:33:04,516
她进城里去了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She went into town.{\r}

1454
01:33:04,591 --> 01:33:06,081
晚上应该能回来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Should be back this evening.{\r}

1455
01:33:06,159 --> 01:33:07,353
呃，鲍勃在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Uh, Bob's here.{\r}

1456
01:33:07,427 --> 01:33:08,485
哦，那好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, good.{\r}

1457
01:33:08,562 --> 01:33:10,894
呃，我是想问你，我能不能在你这里待段时间
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Uh, I was gonna ask if I could stay on a couple days.{\r}

1458
01:33:10,964 --> 01:33:12,329
你要住下？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Staying?{\r}

1459
01:33:12,732 --> 01:33:13,858
对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah.{\r}

1460
01:33:13,934 --> 01:33:16,198
我可不可以用下你的浴室
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Listen, can I use your bathroom?{\r}

1461
01:33:16,269 --> 01:33:18,260
我开了很久的车，想要好好洗个澡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's been a long ride and I could really use a shower.{\r}

1462
01:33:18,338 --> 01:33:20,272
- 当然可以 - 好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course. Okay.{\r}

1463
01:33:21,041 --> 01:33:22,406
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}

1464
01:33:36,790 --> 01:33:38,018
他不是…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Is that...{\r}

1465
01:33:38,224 --> 01:33:41,591
没事的，去隔壁 我会给警察打电话的，快去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, go next door. I'll call the police. Hurry.{\r}

1466
01:33:46,366 --> 01:33:48,061
你好，需要我接什么号码吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Operator. How may I connect you?{\r}

1467
01:33:48,635 --> 01:33:49,693
长官，他就在楼上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's upstairs, sir.{\r}

1468
01:33:49,769 --> 01:33:52,533
从另一边绕过去！截住他！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go around the other side! Cut him off!{\r}

1469
01:33:52,606 --> 01:33:53,664
跟我来！ 是，长官
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come with me! Yes, sir.{\r}

1470
01:33:53,740 --> 01:33:55,037
我们行动！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go!{\r}

1471
01:33:59,212 --> 01:34:03,080
柯林斯太太，我想请你见下我的朋友，哈恩先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins, I'd like you to meet my friend, Mr. Hahn.{\r}

1472
01:34:03,149 --> 01:34:06,778
柯林斯太太，对于你的遭遇我表示深深的遗憾
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins, my deepest condolences on your loss.{\r}

1473
01:34:07,454 --> 01:34:09,012
我们能进来吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}May we come in?{\r}

1474
01:34:13,126 --> 01:34:15,026
谢谢你的关心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I appreciate the sentiment,{\r}

1475
01:34:15,095 --> 01:34:17,325
但是他们说…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}but they've yet to find...{\r}

1476
01:34:17,397 --> 01:34:19,922
已经确认了我儿子的尸体
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}To identify the remains as my son.{\r}

1477
01:34:22,102 --> 01:34:24,593
恐怕没有那么容易放下吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm afraid it never gets any easier.{\r}

1478
01:34:25,171 --> 01:34:27,332
5年前我的女儿因为小儿麻痹症去世了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I lost a daughter to polio five years ago.{\r}

1479
01:34:27,407 --> 01:34:29,602
我每一天，无时无刻不在思念她
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's not a day goes by when I don't think,{\r}

1480
01:34:29,676 --> 01:34:32,201
总是想，我应该把这个告诉克劳蒂
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}"I should mention this to Claudine. "{\r}

1481
01:34:32,278 --> 01:34:34,644
然后我才记起来，她已经不在了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Then I remember she's not here.{\r}

1482
01:34:37,517 --> 01:34:38,814
请坐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please, sit.{\r}

1483
01:34:43,757 --> 01:34:45,691
我今天早上都在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've been on the phone all morning{\r}

1484
01:34:45,759 --> 01:34:48,956
和警察总署的秘书交涉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}with the appointment secretary of the police commission.{\r}

1485
01:34:49,029 --> 01:34:50,997
他们不同意让我出庭作证
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They said that they won't let me testify{\r}

1486
01:34:51,064 --> 01:34:54,329
或者传召证人 说没有这个必要
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}at the hearing or call witnesses. That it won't be necessary.{\r}

1487
01:34:54,401 --> 01:34:56,995
我知道，我听到消息说检查总署
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I know. My sources say the police commission{\r}

1488
01:34:57,070 --> 01:35:01,166
决定宣布说琼斯和洛杉矶警局没有错误
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}is going to say that Jones and the LAPD did absolutely nothing wrong,{\r}

1489
01:35:01,274 --> 01:35:04,334
他们要把责任都推到那个孩子身上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and that the real blame lies with the kid and with you{\r}

1490
01:35:04,411 --> 01:35:09,348
还有你给他们的工作带来了困扰 为了你的个人安全，他们不得不把你隔离
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}for being difficult and forcing them to put you away for your own safety.{\r}

1491
01:35:12,686 --> 01:35:16,850
那样的话我想我需要雇个律师 提起民事诉讼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Then I guess I would have to hire a lawyer, file a civil suit.{\r}

1492
01:35:17,657 --> 01:35:19,591
我找了城里最好的检察官
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I went to the best attorney in town,{\r}

1493
01:35:19,659 --> 01:35:22,492
他和市里面打了4场官司，都赢了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}a man who's sued this city four times and won.{\r}

1494
01:35:22,562 --> 01:35:25,531
可惜的是我们请不起他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Unfortunately, we can't afford to really hire him.{\r}

1495
01:35:25,598 --> 01:35:26,826
我明白
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I see.{\r}

1496
01:35:26,900 --> 01:35:29,391
所以我会接受这个案子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Which is why I'm doing this pro bono.{\r}

1497
01:35:29,936 --> 01:35:33,269
很荣幸能够为你辩护，柯林斯太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It would be my honor to defend your honor, Mrs. Collins.{\r}

1498
01:35:33,473 --> 01:35:34,838
在我做律师的15年里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}In my 15 years as a lawyer,{\r}

1499
01:35:34,908 --> 01:35:38,708
从没有见过任何人像你这样坚持又倔强地争斗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have never seen anyone fight as long or as hard as you have,{\r}

1500
01:35:38,945 --> 01:35:42,108
毫无疑问，正义站在你这一边
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}in what is so clearly in the cause of justice.{\r}

1501
01:35:42,882 --> 01:35:44,247
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}

1502
01:35:44,818 --> 01:35:46,183
让我看看，书架上有什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me see what's on the shelf.{\r}

1503
01:35:46,252 --> 01:35:47,583
我来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll look.{\r}

1504
01:35:49,656 --> 01:35:50,748
你好？我可不可以…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes? May I...{\r}

1505
01:35:50,824 --> 01:35:52,155
我叫S.S.哈恩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My name is S.S. Hahn,{\r}

1506
01:35:52,225 --> 01:35:55,058
我手上有法庭的执行令 要求你们释放所有因为第12条行政令
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and I have a court order for the immediate release of all women being detained{\r}

1507
01:35:55,128 --> 01:35:58,063
而被关押进这家机构的所有女性
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}in this institution under the designation code 12{\r}

1508
01:35:58,131 --> 01:36:01,362
并就将他们关押的理由的正当性提出质疑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}pending a formal inquiry into the reasons for their detainment.{\r}

1509
01:36:01,434 --> 01:36:03,595
对不起，主管医生现在不在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry, the doctor in charge is not here{\r}

1510
01:36:03,670 --> 01:36:05,194
大概要等到早上 女士，我清楚地和你说吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}until the morning. Madam, let me be clearer.{\r}

1511
01:36:05,271 --> 01:36:08,035
要不你就乖乖地照执行令说的给我名单
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Either you will produce the people named in that court order,{\r}

1512
01:36:08,108 --> 01:36:11,669
要不然你会发现自己出现在铁栏杆后 而且是没有钥匙孔的那边
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}or you will find yourself behind bars, and I mean without a key.{\r}

1513
01:36:11,745 --> 01:36:14,873
我没有权限给你… 女士，请让一让
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't authorize you... Madam, stand aside.{\r}

1514
01:36:24,858 --> 01:36:25,916
我能见她了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Can I see her now?{\r}

1515
01:36:25,992 --> 01:36:28,017
当然，没问题 她怎么样了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sure. Absolutely. How does she look?{\r}

1516
01:36:53,653 --> 01:36:55,621
好了，朋友们，都退后 给他让条路
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, fellas, step back. Let's give him room.{\r}

1517
01:36:55,688 --> 01:36:56,712
他在这里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Here he is.{\r}

1518
01:36:56,790 --> 01:36:58,781
诺斯考特先生 关于被捕，请你说几句
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Northcott, any comment on your arrest?{\r}

1519
01:36:58,858 --> 01:37:00,018
诺斯考特先生 你现在是怎么想的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Northcott, how are you feeling?{\r}

1520
01:37:00,093 --> 01:37:01,754
哦，我觉得挺不错的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, I'm feeling fine.{\r}

1521
01:37:01,828 --> 01:37:04,353
正如你们所知道的，我度了个小假
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've been on a little vacation, as some of you know.{\r}

1522
01:37:04,430 --> 01:37:07,126
是个非常愉快的假期
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It was a really pleasant vacation.{\r}

1523
01:37:07,200 --> 01:37:10,431
最近警察和我找了不少乐子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The police have certainly provided me with a lot of amusement.{\r}

1524
01:37:10,503 --> 01:37:11,936
你躲了多久？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How long you been in hiding?{\r}

1525
01:37:12,005 --> 01:37:13,267
你是怎么逃过警察追捕的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How did you avoid capture?{\r}

1526
01:37:13,339 --> 01:37:14,601
别吵，别吵，都问够了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Easy, easy. That's far enough.{\r}

1527
01:37:14,674 --> 01:37:16,369
是吗，我可没有，对吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, I didn't, did I?{\r}

1528
01:37:16,442 --> 01:37:17,534
再来一张！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}One more shot!{\r}

1529
01:37:17,610 --> 01:37:19,578
你见到报纸上自己的照片了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you seen your picture in the paper?{\r}

1530
01:37:19,646 --> 01:37:22,877
我直到最近才知道有人要抓我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Didn't know anybody wanted me until just recently.{\r}

1531
01:37:22,949 --> 01:37:24,541
我没有逃
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Didn't even try.{\r}

1532
01:37:25,151 --> 01:37:28,211
伙计，我的行李上还有我的名字缩写呢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My luggage still has my initials on it, fellas.{\r}

1533
01:37:28,288 --> 01:37:30,415
你知道警察为什么要抓你吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you know why the police were after you?{\r}

1534
01:37:30,490 --> 01:37:33,391
不知道，不过如果能不沾染上官司 我觉得会更好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, but I figured it'd be a good idea if I were to just stay out of it.{\r}

1535
01:37:33,459 --> 01:37:34,483
你感到羞愧吗？先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Any remorse, sir?{\r}

1536
01:37:34,561 --> 01:37:39,260
你有什么话要对被你谋杀的孩子的父母说吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you have anything to say to the parents of the children you murdered?{\r}

1537
01:37:39,332 --> 01:37:41,027
无可奉告
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No comment.{\r}

1538
01:37:41,100 --> 01:37:42,192
再拍一张 看这里！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}One more shot, this way!{\r}

1539
01:37:43,803 --> 01:37:46,465
克雷尔市长，事情太出人意料了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mayor Cryer. This is unexpected.{\r}

1540
01:37:47,340 --> 01:37:48,864
的确
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So was this.{\r}

1541
01:37:48,942 --> 01:37:52,378
传票，要求宣誓证词, 接受问讯.
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Subpoenas, requests for depositions, interrogatories.{\r}

