1546
01:38:03,957 --> 01:38:05,015
马上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}starting immediately.{\r}

1547
01:38:05,091 --> 01:38:06,149
该死的！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}God damn it!{\r}

1548
01:38:06,226 --> 01:38:08,956
我还以为事情总算过去了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I thought this was supposed to go away.{\r}

1549
01:38:09,596 --> 01:38:10,824
今年是选举年
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is an election year.{\r}

1550
01:38:10,897 --> 01:38:12,387
我可不想闹出这么大的负面新闻来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't afford this kind of press.{\r}

1551
01:38:12,465 --> 01:38:15,696
很快就会解决的，我已经告诉琼斯上尉怎么做了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It is going away, sir. I've instructed Captain Jones to deal with it.{\r}

1552
01:38:15,768 --> 01:38:17,326
我担心的是，就算他低声下气
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm afraid, falling on his sword{\r}

1553
01:38:17,403 --> 01:38:21,305
道歉说他犯了错，也没法弥补了，局长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and saying he made a mistake isn't going to be good enough, Chief.{\r}

1554
01:38:21,374 --> 01:38:24,832
我们让他躲一阵子风头
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}If we take him out of the picture for a while,{\r}

1555
01:38:24,911 --> 01:38:28,711
直到庭审结束，等事情冷下来会比较好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}just might help calm things down until the hearing's finished.{\r}

1556
01:38:46,366 --> 01:38:48,664
发生了什么事？ 你没有听说吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What is happening? Didn't you hear?{\r}

1557
01:38:48,735 --> 01:38:50,498
这是我见过的最庞大的抗议队伍了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's the biggest protest I've ever seen.{\r}

1558
01:38:50,570 --> 01:38:51,832
抗议 对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Protest? Yeah.{\r}

1559
01:38:51,905 --> 01:38:55,102
都是支持柯林斯的 让人难以置信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Over the Collins broad, if you can believe that.{\r}

1560
01:39:04,684 --> 01:39:07,847
我们要公正！ 我们要公正！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We want justice! We want justice!{\r}

1561
01:39:10,256 --> 01:39:11,848
哦，天啊！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, my!{\r}

1562
01:39:18,331 --> 01:39:20,299
哈里斯先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Harris.{\r}

1563
01:39:20,366 --> 01:39:23,665
上帝的行事必然有他的道理，柯林斯太太
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The Lord works in mysterious ways, Mrs. Collins.{\r}

1564
01:39:24,904 --> 01:39:26,769
真的吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Boy, does he ever.{\r}

1565
01:39:44,057 --> 01:39:46,651
女士们，先生们，请听我说
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Ladies and gentlemen, can I have your attention, please?{\r}

1566
01:39:46,726 --> 01:39:51,288
这是有史以来参庭人数最多的一次
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There are more people gathered in this chamber than have ever been in this room before.{\r}

1567
01:39:51,364 --> 01:39:55,061
所以我想请你们稍微克制一下你们的举动
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Therefore, I ask you to refrain from demonstrations of any kind.{\r}

1568
01:39:55,134 --> 01:39:56,624
告诉我们真相！告诉我们真相！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell the truth! Tell the truth!{\r}

1569
01:39:56,703 --> 01:40:00,605
我们聚集在这里是因为我们都想知道事实的真相
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We are all here because we want to know the real facts in this case.{\r}

1570
01:40:00,673 --> 01:40:04,803
我想一周之后，我们就能够知道事情的真相了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And everybody is going to be heard if we have to sit here for a week.{\r}

1571
01:40:04,877 --> 01:40:07,778
索普先生，我怎么没有看到警察总署的人？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Thorpe, I don't see any members of the police commission.{\r}

1572
01:40:11,284 --> 01:40:14,447
房间里有谁是警局的代表吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Are there any members of the police department in the room?{\r}

1573
01:40:14,520 --> 01:40:16,385
戴维斯局长在吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Is Chief Davis here?{\r}

1574
01:40:17,790 --> 01:40:19,382
琼斯上尉来了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Is Captain Jones here?{\r}

1575
01:40:21,160 --> 01:40:22,559
这里有谁是代表警察的吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Is there anybody here representing the police?{\r}

1576
01:40:22,628 --> 01:40:26,826
柯林斯太太，请你和我一起到外面去下可以吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins, could you come across the street with me for just a moment?{\r}

1577
01:40:26,899 --> 01:40:29,094
我想你应该看看这个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's something I think you should see.{\r}

1578
01:40:29,168 --> 01:40:31,193
好吧，虽然我不希望在开庭前就要求中止
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, I hate to call a recess before we've even started,{\r}

1579
01:40:31,270 --> 01:40:32,794
不过我想我得先打几个电话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}but I think a few phone calls are in order.{\r}

1580
01:40:37,043 --> 01:40:39,944
警察方面希望审判能够在非公开的场合进行
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The police decided it'd be best to keep this off the main docket{\r}

1581
01:40:40,046 --> 01:40:44,278
以免出现街对面那样的混乱局面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}in order to avoid exactly the sort of chaos we have across the street.{\r}

1582
01:40:56,929 --> 01:40:59,898
柯林斯太太 我是莉安・克雷
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mrs. Collins. I'm Leanne Clay.{\r}

1583
01:41:00,700 --> 01:41:02,964
这是我的丈夫，约翰 你好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is my husband, John. Hi.{\r}

1584
01:41:03,870 --> 01:41:06,896
我只是想表达我的同情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I just wanted to pass along my sympathies.{\r}

1585
01:41:07,173 --> 01:41:09,300
我们以为自己儿子戴维的消息已经够糟糕了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What we went through waiting to hear anything{\r}

1586
01:41:09,375 --> 01:41:13,505
结果现在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}about our son David was bad enough, now this.{\r}

1587
01:41:14,447 --> 01:41:18,406
警察们对你的所作所为，实在是令人发指
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But what the police did to you, there was no call for that.{\r}

1588
01:41:18,484 --> 01:41:20,042
太过分了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No call at all.{\r}

1589
01:41:23,056 --> 01:41:24,614
请起立
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All rise.{\r}

1590
01:41:33,366 --> 01:41:35,391
请大家都坐下 法警
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please, be seated. Bailiff.{\r}

1591
01:41:48,648 --> 01:41:49,842
哦，嘿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, hey.{\r}

1592
01:41:52,051 --> 01:41:54,178
我在报纸上看到你了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I saw you in the papers.{\r}

1593
01:41:54,253 --> 01:41:58,121
你真的很有胆量，敢跟这样的警察作对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You got a lot of moxie, standing up to the police like that.{\r}

1594
01:42:03,329 --> 01:42:05,263
请被告起立
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The defendant will please rise.{\r}

1595
01:42:10,903 --> 01:42:12,996
高顿・斯图尔特・诺斯考特,
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Gordon Stewart Northcott,{\r}

1596
01:42:13,072 --> 01:42:17,236
你被指控犯有3宗一级谋杀
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}you've been charged with three counts of murder in the first degree,{\r}

1597
01:42:17,310 --> 01:42:22,009
另有17项未确认指控正在接受地区检察官的调查
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}with an additional 17 counts under review by the district attorney's office.{\r}

1598
01:42:22,081 --> 01:42:23,708
你可认罪？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How do you plea?{\r}

1599
01:42:25,118 --> 01:42:27,245
我没有罪，法官大人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, not guilty, Your Honor.{\r}

1600
01:42:31,023 --> 01:42:33,184
诺斯考特先生，请坐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You may sit, Mr. Northcott.{\r}

1601
01:42:37,763 --> 01:42:42,700
考虑到被告喜欢进行跨国旅行，所以不允许保释
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}In light of the defendant's penchant for international travel, no bail will be set.{\r}

1602
01:42:42,768 --> 01:42:45,362
法庭会在明天造成听取初步动议
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This court will hear preliminary motions by tomorrow morning.{\r}

1603
01:42:45,438 --> 01:42:47,906
一名叫作沃特・柯林斯的男孩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The boy, Walter Collins,{\r}

1604
01:42:47,974 --> 01:42:50,738
在1928年3月10日失踪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}was reported as missing, March 10, 1928.{\r}

1605
01:42:51,544 --> 01:42:54,172
之后我们进行了全国性的搜索
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We then instituted a nationwide search.{\r}

1606
01:42:54,247 --> 01:42:58,183
在8月18日，我们接到一个电话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}On August 18th, we received a cable indicating that a boy{\r}

1607
01:42:58,251 --> 01:43:01,687
告知在伊利诺斯州，德卡博发现了一名 符合他外貌特征的男孩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}matching his description was found in DeKalb, Illinois.{\r}

1608
01:43:01,754 --> 01:43:05,781
经过问讯，他承认自己是沃特・柯林斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Upon questioning, he admitted to being Walter Collins.{\r}

1609
01:43:05,858 --> 01:43:10,818
我们安排这个孩子坐火车回到了加利福尼亚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We then made arrangements for him to be transported back to California.{\r}

1610
01:43:11,063 --> 01:43:13,531
之后柯林斯太太告诉你说那个男孩不是她的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Where Mrs. Collins told you the boy was not her son.{\r}

1611
01:43:13,599 --> 01:43:15,362
是的，她拒绝承认
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes. She denied his identity{\r}

1612
01:43:15,434 --> 01:43:18,426
而各项证据都证明这孩子是她的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}in spite of all of the evidence pointing to the contrary.{\r}

1613
01:43:18,504 --> 01:43:21,598
但是后来的种种迹象表明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But, as subsequent events have demonstrated,{\r}

1614
01:43:21,707 --> 01:43:23,368
她说的是对的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}she was correct.{\r}

1615
01:43:24,610 --> 01:43:26,475
那么，出于什么原因
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, what prompted you to send her{\r}

1616
01:43:26,546 --> 01:43:28,173
你要将她送去接受心理检查呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}for psychological evaluation?{\r}

1617
01:43:28,247 --> 01:43:29,976
这个孩子是不是她的孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Whether or not this was in fact the correct boy{\r}

1618
01:43:30,049 --> 01:43:32,574
和我的决定没有关系
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}was not relevant to my decision.{\r}

1619
01:43:32,652 --> 01:43:34,813
在那段时间里，她的行为十分怪异
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Throughout this period, she acted strangely.{\r}

1620
01:43:34,887 --> 01:43:38,414
她表现的很冷酷，淡漠，面无表情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She was often cool and aloof and unemotional,{\r}

1621
01:43:38,491 --> 01:43:42,154
特别是面对我们在德卡博找到的男孩时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}especially when confronted with the boy we found in DeKalb{\r}

1622
01:43:42,228 --> 01:43:44,287
以及在我们后续的交谈中
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and in our subsequent conversation.{\r}

1623
01:43:44,363 --> 01:43:46,228
她的种种奇怪表现
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It was because of her{\r}

1624
01:43:47,033 --> 01:43:51,732
所以我同意将她送去洛杉矶综合医院
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}disturbing behavior that I submitted her for observation{\r}

1625
01:43:51,804 --> 01:43:54,602
在精神病院接受看护
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}to the psychopathic ward of Los Angeles County General Hospital.{\r}

1626
01:43:54,674 --> 01:43:55,971
就这么一下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Just like that.{\r}

1627
01:43:56,042 --> 01:43:58,237
你只不过打了个响指
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You snap your fingers and an innocent woman{\r}

1628
01:43:58,311 --> 01:44:00,006
就把一个无辜的女人丢进了精神病院！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}is thrown into the psycho ward!{\r}

1629
01:44:00,079 --> 01:44:03,412
- 不是被强制的 - 如果任何一个警察上尉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She wasn't thrown. Every family in this state is in grave danger{\r}

1630
01:44:03,482 --> 01:44:06,610
都可以用职权 在5分钟内将一个刚进入他办公室的女人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}when a police captain can take a woman into his office{\r}

1631
01:44:06,719 --> 01:44:08,016
强制送进精神病院的话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and five minutes later{\r}

1632
01:44:08,087 --> 01:44:10,817
恐怕这个州的每一个家庭正受到这潜在的威胁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}have her thrown into the psychopathic ward on his own authority!{\r}

1633
01:44:10,890 --> 01:44:12,289
她不算是被强迫的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She wasn't thrown.{\r}

1634
01:44:12,358 --> 01:44:15,691
我们没有强迫她！ 她不算是被强迫进去的！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She wasn't thrown! She wasn't thrown!{\r}

1635
01:44:16,362 --> 01:44:18,262
那是怎么样的呢？队长？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What was that, Captain?{\r}

1636
01:44:18,864 --> 01:44:21,059
我们没有强制遣送她 她是被护送入院的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She wasn't thrown. She was escorted.{\r}

1637
01:44:24,804 --> 01:44:28,331
护送，强制，用什么样的动词都没有区别，上尉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Escorted, thrown, the verb doesn't matter, Captain.{\r}

1638
01:44:28,407 --> 01:44:32,639
问题在于她是在没有逮捕令的情况下被关押的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What does matter is that her incarceration was ordered without a warrant.{\r}

1639
01:44:32,712 --> 01:44:34,646
我这里有一份洛杉矶州就克莉斯汀・柯林斯一案
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I am holding a carbon copy{\r}

1640
01:44:34,714 --> 01:44:37,842
下发的精神错乱鉴定证词
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}of the affidavit of insanity that was issued in the case{\r}

1641
01:44:37,917 --> 01:44:41,353
的文件副本
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}of the State of California v. Christine Collins.{\r}

1642
01:44:41,420 --> 01:44:42,887
这份证词是谁签的字？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Who signed the affidavit?{\r}

1643
01:44:42,955 --> 01:44:44,047
是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I did.{\r}

1644
01:44:44,123 --> 01:44:46,751
好吧，那么让我看下这个说法对不对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, now, let me see if I have this correct,{\r}

1645
01:44:46,826 --> 01:44:50,421
你们在没有逮捕令的情况下将一个女人关进精神病院里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}a woman was thrown into the psychopathic ward without a warrant,{\r}

1646
01:44:50,496 --> 01:44:52,657
因为根本没有所谓的逮捕令存在
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}because no warrant existed.{\r}

1647
01:44:52,732 --> 01:44:55,292
等到逮捕令写好已经是几天之后了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And when it was finally written several days later,{\r}

1648
01:44:55,368 --> 01:44:57,734
那时候她人已经被关进病院里去了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}there was no need to sign it or to go to a judge{\r}

1649
01:44:57,803 --> 01:45:00,567
也就不需要再签发或者向法官提交了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}because she was already in the asylum!{\r}

1650
01:45:02,241 --> 01:45:03,333
是这样吧，上尉先生？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Is this correct, Captain?{\r}

1651
01:45:03,409 --> 01:45:04,671
理论上来说，是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Technically, yes.{\r}

1652
01:45:04,744 --> 01:45:07,770
有时候非常规手段是必须的，因为我们是在处理…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Extraordinary steps were necessary because we were dealing...{\r}

1653
