{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They found him up in Hesperia.{\r}

2010
02:08:53,104 --> 02:08:56,096
你从学校回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You were walking home from school,{\r}

2011
02:08:56,174 --> 02:08:58,369
然后他们说让你帮忙找一只狗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and they told you they needed help finding a dog.{\r}

2012
02:08:58,443 --> 02:08:59,705
是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah.{\r}

2013
02:08:59,777 --> 02:09:02,837
那么，你上了卡车之后，发生了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, after you got in the truck, what happened next?{\r}

2014
02:09:02,914 --> 02:09:05,212
他们开车带我逛了好多时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They drove me around for a long time,{\r}

2015
02:09:05,283 --> 02:09:06,841
最后我们在这个农场停了下来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}then we ended up at this ranch.{\r}

2016
02:09:06,984 --> 02:09:10,385
过来 戴夫，过来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on. Come on, Davy.{\r}

2017
02:09:10,455 --> 02:09:11,820
- 戴夫！过来 - 放开我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Davy! Come on. Get off me.{\r}

2018
02:09:11,889 --> 02:09:13,083
别打架！ 别吵
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't fight this much. Hey!{\r}

2019
02:09:13,157 --> 02:09:15,250
那里还有别的男孩吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Were there other boys there?{\r}

2020
02:09:15,960 --> 02:09:18,428
是的，我记得还有5个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah. Five, I think.{\r}

2021
02:09:19,997 --> 02:09:21,931
不过，那是很久之前了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It was a long time ago, though.{\r}

2022
02:09:21,999 --> 02:09:24,297
嗨，孩子们 这是戴夫！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, boys. This is Davy.{\r}

2023
02:09:24,368 --> 02:09:25,733
我知道你们会… 嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I know you'll make him feel... Hey!{\r}

2024
02:09:26,904 --> 02:09:30,237
不，不，嘿！ 闭嘴！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No. No! Hey! Shut up!{\r}

2025
02:09:30,308 --> 02:09:32,208
你和他们说过话吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you speak to them?{\r}

2026
02:09:32,977 --> 02:09:35,571
说了？那你还记得他们的名字吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah? You remember any of their names?{\r}

2027
02:09:36,447 --> 02:09:38,415
嗯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah.{\r}

2028
02:09:38,483 --> 02:09:39,916
他们中有两个是兄弟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Two of them were brothers.{\r}

2029
02:09:39,984 --> 02:09:42,817
我想他们应该是姓文斯洛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I think their last name was Winslow.{\r}

2030
02:09:44,122 --> 02:09:46,215
大的那个应该叫杰佛瑞
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The oldest one was Jeffrey.{\r}

2031
02:09:50,194 --> 02:09:51,684
还有个叫沃特.
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And Walter.{\r}

2032
02:09:54,098 --> 02:09:55,622
沃特？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Walter?{\r}

2033
02:09:56,400 --> 02:09:59,301
你还记得沃特的姓吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah. Do you remember Walter's last name?{\r}

2034
02:10:04,742 --> 02:10:06,004
柯林斯.
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Collins.{\r}

2035
02:10:07,678 --> 02:10:09,236
沃特・柯林斯.
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Walter Collins.{\r}

2036
02:10:10,281 --> 02:10:13,512
你只记得这些男孩的名字？还记得别的事吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell me something if you only remember some of the boys' names,{\r}

2037
02:10:13,584 --> 02:10:16,246
你怎么会记得他的全名的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}how come you remember his full name?{\r}

2038
02:10:16,988 --> 02:10:19,115
因为发生的事情？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Because of what happened.{\r}

2039
02:10:19,190 --> 02:10:21,215
沃特和杰佛瑞在说话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Walter and Jeffrey were talking.{\r}

2040
02:10:21,292 --> 02:10:23,226
- 拉起来 - 因为他们检查了周围
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Pull it. They kept checking around{\r}

2041
02:10:23,294 --> 02:10:25,888
他们发现棚子旁边有块栅栏松了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}and they found a part of the coop where the wire was all messed up.{\r}

2042
02:10:25,963 --> 02:10:27,555
当心！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Be careful!{\r}

2043
02:10:27,632 --> 02:10:29,327
快点！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hurry!{\r}

2044
02:10:29,400 --> 02:10:31,766
也许我们能够挖个足够大的洞，然后逃出去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe make enough room to get out of there and run.{\r}

2045
02:10:31,836 --> 02:10:33,531
我们跑出来以后就分开走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}When we get out, we split up,{\r}

2046
02:10:33,604 --> 02:10:35,367
朝不同的方向跑，明白了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}go in different directions. Okay?{\r}

2047
02:10:35,439 --> 02:10:37,532
他们没法抓住我们所有人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They can't catch all of us.{\r}

2048
02:10:37,608 --> 02:10:39,576
肯定弄出了很多声响
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It'd make an awful lot of noise.{\r}

2049
02:10:39,644 --> 02:10:42,374
轻点，明白吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Be quiet. You got it?{\r}

2050
02:10:42,446 --> 02:10:45,347
结果那个洞不够大，所以我们卡住了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And if it wasn't wide enough, then we'd be stuck.{\r}

2051
02:10:48,719 --> 02:10:51,916
等等，救命！帮帮我！ 快点，快点走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wait. Help! Help! Come on, hurry!{\r}

2052
02:10:52,824 --> 02:10:56,123
我的脚卡住了，快点 救命，帮帮我！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My foot's stuck! Hurry, help! Help me, please!{\r}

2053
02:10:58,696 --> 02:11:01,563
他过来了！ 他…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's coming! He's...{\r}

2054
02:11:01,632 --> 02:11:03,293
我的脚！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My foot!{\r}

2055
02:11:04,235 --> 02:11:05,759
他过来了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's coming.{\r}

2056
02:11:05,837 --> 02:11:07,600
快点，快跑，跑！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hurry, run, run, run!{\r}

2057
02:11:12,710 --> 02:11:15,201
嘿，你们这群小混蛋
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey! What the hell are you boys...{\r}

2058
02:11:17,081 --> 02:11:21,711
哦！圣母玛丽亚！嘿！嘿！嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh! Mary, Mother of God! Hey! Hey! Hey!{\r}

2059
02:11:22,453 --> 02:11:25,513
你们滚回来！ 嘿！站住！嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You get back here! Hey! Hold it! Hey!{\r}

2060
02:11:27,992 --> 02:11:29,084
嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey!{\r}

2061
02:11:30,261 --> 02:11:31,319
嘿！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey!{\r}

2062
02:11:32,530 --> 02:11:34,157
别跑！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}

2063
02:11:36,500 --> 02:11:37,865
去抓其他的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Check on the others!{\r}

2064
02:11:37,935 --> 02:11:39,334
站住！该死的！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop! Damn it!{\r}

2065
02:11:39,403 --> 02:11:41,667
臭小子们，我跟着你们了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Boys, I'm coming after you!{\r}

2066
02:11:41,739 --> 02:11:44,833
该死！该死!
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn it! Damn it!{\r}

2067
02:11:45,142 --> 02:11:48,077
小家伙们，不管你们跑到哪里，我都会找到你们的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Boys, I'll find you no matter where you are!{\r}

2068
02:11:48,145 --> 02:11:50,511
他们不在这里了 过来，上车！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They're not in there! Come on! Get in the car!{\r}

2069
02:11:50,581 --> 02:11:54,711
我会找到你们的！该死的！ 快点上车，他妈的！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm gonna find you! Damn it! Damn it! Come on.{\r}

2070
02:11:54,785 --> 02:11:57,185
妈的！上车！ 桑佛德！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Shit! Get in the car, Sanford!{\r}

2071
02:12:04,662 --> 02:12:07,290
那是我最后一次看到他们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That was the last I saw of any of them.{\r}

2072
02:12:07,865 --> 02:12:10,891
也就是说你也不知道另外两个人后来有没被抓住？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, you don't know if either of the other two were captured?{\r}

2073
02:12:10,968 --> 02:12:12,060
不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

2074
02:12:13,337 --> 02:12:15,237
我知道的是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All I know is,{\r}

2075
02:12:15,306 --> 02:12:18,173
如果没有沃特回来找我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}if Walter hadn't come back for me{\r}

2076
02:12:19,043 --> 02:12:21,773
我大概永远没有机会逃出来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think I ever would've gotten out of there.{\r}

2077
02:12:22,680 --> 02:12:24,045
好吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay.{\r}

2078
02:12:25,316 --> 02:12:27,477
之后发生了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, what happened after that?{\r}

2079
02:12:27,551 --> 02:12:29,246
我朝着大路一直跑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I kept off the main roads,{\r}

2080
02:12:29,320 --> 02:12:34,280
然后看到火车在岔道口听了下来 就跳了上去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}until I saw a train stopped at a crossing and I jumped in.{\r}

2081
02:12:34,692 --> 02:12:37,752
你为什么不告诉别人发生了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why didn't you tell anyone what had happened?{\r}

2082
02:12:37,828 --> 02:12:39,295
我害怕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I was afraid.{\r}

2083
02:12:39,797 --> 02:12:42,766
我以为他们回来抓我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I thought they'd come after me, or my folks.{\r}

2084
02:12:44,568 --> 02:12:47,002
所以我谁都没有告诉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So, I just didn't tell anybody.{\r}

2085
02:12:48,873 --> 02:12:53,071
我一直是一个人待着 后来有位蓝欣小姐给我免费的饭吃
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I was on my own until I got a free meal from this lady, Miss Lansing.{\r}

2086
02:12:53,144 --> 02:12:55,635
我告诉她说我是个孤儿，就一个人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Told her I was an orphan, on my own.{\r}

2087
02:12:57,615 --> 02:12:59,606
她说我可以留下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She said I could stay on.{\r}

2088
02:13:01,052 --> 02:13:02,383
于是我就待了下来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I did.{\r}

2089
02:13:03,621 --> 02:13:04,986
每个晚上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Every night,{\r}

2090
02:13:05,056 --> 02:13:08,492
我都会惊醒，以为他们就在窗外等我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd wake up thinking they were right outside my window.{\r}

2091
02:13:09,026 --> 02:13:11,494
然后我在广播里听警察说了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And then I heard the police talking on the radio{\r}

2092
02:13:11,562 --> 02:13:14,326
在农场里发生的事情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}about what happened at the ranch.{\r}

2093
02:13:14,432 --> 02:13:16,798
于是我想，现在我大概可以回家了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I thought, "For sure I can't go back now. "{\r}

2094
02:13:16,867 --> 02:13:18,334
为什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why?{\r}

2095
02:13:18,869 --> 02:13:19,927
为什么不回家？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why not?{\r}

2096
02:13:20,004 --> 02:13:22,802
因为我没有告诉任何人发生过什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Since I didn't tell anybody what happened.{\r}

2097
02:13:24,175 --> 02:13:26,939
我害怕他们会骂我 会为了那些孩子的死怪我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I was afraid they'd blame me for those kids being dead.{\r}

2098
02:13:28,846 --> 02:13:30,711
所以我一直躲在外面不敢回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So I just stayed away.{\r}

2099
02:13:32,450 --> 02:13:35,442
那这么多年之后，你为什么现在回来了呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What made you come forward now, after all this time?{\r}

2100
02:13:35,519 --> 02:13:38,079
嗯？为什么现在找警察？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hmm? Why come forward now?{\r}

2101
02:13:41,659 --> 02:13:43,422
我真的很想我妈妈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I really miss my mom.{\r}

2102
02:13:45,830 --> 02:13:47,730
我真的很想我爸爸
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I really miss my dad.{\r}

2103
02:13:50,768 --> 02:13:52,736
我想回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I just wanna go home.{\r}

2104
02:13:56,140 --> 02:13:57,937
我只想回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I just wanna go home.{\r}

2105
02:14:03,948 --> 02:14:05,711
你还好吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you all right?{\r}

2106
02:14:06,384 --> 02:14:08,579
我爱你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I love you.{\r}

2107
02:14:41,085 --> 02:14:42,848
我还是不敢相信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I still can't believe it.{\r}

2108
02:14:42,920 --> 02:14:46,822
案子已经结束5年了，大家都以为他死了 然后他又出现了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Five years, case closed, everyone thinks he's dead, and there he is.{\r}

2109
02:14:48,325 --> 02:14:51,089
如果没有沃特的话，他肯定回不来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wouldn't be, if it wasn't for Walter.{\r}

2110
02:14:52,763 --> 02:14:55,323
柯林斯太太，你的儿子很勇敢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your son did a brave thing, Mrs. Collins.{\r}

2111
02:14:55,399 --> 02:14:57,594
你应该为他骄傲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You should be very proud of him.{\r}

2112
02:14:57,668 --> 02:14:58,999
我为他骄傲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I am.{\r}

2113
02:15:01,338 --> 02:15:02,896
你觉得他还活着？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You still think he's out there?{\r}

2114
02:15:02,973 --> 02:15:04,201
为什么不？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why not?{\r}

2115
02:15:05,443 --> 02:15:07,411
警探先生，那天晚上有三个孩子逃了出去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Three boys made a run for it that night, Detective.{\r}

2116
02:15:07,478 --> 02:15:09,002
如果一个人逃脱了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And if one got out,{\r}

2117
02:15:09,080 --> 02:15:12,174
那么其他两个人中至少会有一个能逃出来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}then maybe either or both of the others did, too.{\r}

2118
02:15:12,249 --> 02:15:15,810
沃特可能也逃了出来，而且和这个孩子一样 他心里害怕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe Walter's out there, having the same fears that he did.{\r}

2119
02:15:15,920 --> 02:15:17,785
不敢公开自己的身份，也不敢回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Afraid to come home and identify himself,{\r}

2120
02:15:17,855 --> 02:15:20,255
或者是害怕自己会再惹上麻烦
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}or afraid he'll get into trouble.{\r}

2121
02:15:21,692 --> 02:15:23,785
不管是哪种情况
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But either way,{\r}

2122
02:15:23,861 --> 02:15:26,989
今天晚上的事给了我一些以前没有的东西
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}it gives me something I didn't have before tonight.{\r}

2123
02:15:27,098 --> 02:15:28,497
是什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's that?{\r}

2124
02:15:29,467 --> 02:15:30,661
希望
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hope.{\r}

2125
02:16:02,467 --> 02:16:07,661
庭审结束后,琼斯上尉被停职,戴维斯局长被撤职 克雷尔市长没有得到再次参加竞选的机会
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

2126
02:16:09,467 --> 02:16:14,661
布里格勒博牧师继续用他的电台节目 揭露警察的不端行为和政要的收贿受贿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

2127
02:16:15,467 --> 02:16:20,661
为了消弭丑闻带来的影响 加利福尼亚的怀恩威尔更名为米拉罗马
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

